, </div><div class="t m62b x36 h2d y29bd ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">who lived from </div><div class="t m2d9d xa4 h15 y29bd ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A. D. </div><div class="t m6a6 x89 h2d y29bd ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">354 to 43o. </div><div class="t m101 x66 h2d y23fa ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">zo. What did he teach ? </div><div class="t m291 x99 h4a y2a00 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ans.--&quot; </div><div class="t m254 xb0 h2d y2a04 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It is indeed </div><div class="t m146 x36 h2d y28ce ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">better that men should he brought to serve </div><div class="t m1c5 x36 h2d y1b56 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God by instruction than by fear of punish-</div><div class="t m6b7 x36 h2d y204d ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ment or by pain. But because the former </div><div class="t m811 x36 h2d y1435 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">means are better, the latter must not therefore </div><div class="t m104b x36 h2d y10b4 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">be neglected. . . . Many must often be </div><div class="t m66d x36 h2d ybad ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">brought back to their Lord, like wicked serv-</div><div class="t m235 x36 h2d y1367 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ants, by the rod of temporal suffering, before </div><div class="t m195 x28 h2d y10b7 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">they attain to the highest grade of religious </div><div class="t m6e8 x36 h2d ye99 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">development.&quot;—Schaff&apos;s </div><div class="t m874 x2e h4a ybaf ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Church History, sec. </div><div class="t m704 x36 h30 y10c0 ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">27; </div><div class="t m2fb x55 h4a ybce ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Augustine Epistle 185 ad Bonifacium, sec. </div><div class="t m159f x28 h30 y104a ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">21, 24. </div><div class="t m34ca x66 h15 y1335 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">21. </div><div class="t m6e8 x35 h2d y1335 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What does Neander say of this? </div><div class="t mac1 xb3 h4a y11c2 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ans. </div><di